There is no doubt that these research projects, the developing ideas, and the related forms of so- cial action were influenced most, fundamentally by the psychodynamic theories of Alfred Adler. The late Francis Cecil Sunnier, Professor of Psychology at Howard University, introduced me to the ideas of Adlcr. It was Professor Sumner who first intro- duced me as an undergraduate to the promises of the science of psychology for the understanding of man and society. It was he who gave me my first serious appreciation of the complexities of the meanings of humanity. In his characteristic style, Professor Sumner presented Adler's thoughts with- in the framework of other psychoanalytic and psychodynamic theories and within the larger con- text of religion and philosophy. This experience had a profound influence on my thoughts, research, and professional and personal action.
