If there is no convincing evidence that schizophrenia is an identifiable disease, there is far less scientific support for a sickness model explanation of all of the less extreme forms of human deviation, yet the American Psychiatric Association keeps issuing posi- tion statements claiming responsibility for such conditions as mental retardation, ju- ~enile delinquency, and alcoholism. The
